This paper is about improving the efficiency of neural machine translation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of embedding-based selection methods, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper explores the trade-offs between speed and accuracy, which is a common concern in artificial intelligence (AI) and optimization, making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of CPUs, which is a common hardware platform for neural networks and falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the WMT15 and WMT16 datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and NLP research, making cs.CV another possible sub-category.
